<subSubSection id="9A85652DFFD6FFE6B0AFFC5EE4F4FA15" pageId="2" pageNumber="5" type="description">
<paragraph id="D22036A6FFD6FFE6B0AFFC5EE439FB95" blockId="2.[166,1226,981,1424]" pageId="2" pageNumber="5">
F e m a l e. Head with antennae 
<quantity id="15679B43FFD6FFE6B23CFC5EE4F8FC75" box="[584,666,981,1008]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.3" pageId="2" pageNumber="5" unit="mm" value="23.0">23 mm</quantity>
long. Forewings 
<quantity id="15679B43FFD6FFE6B316FC5EE5D7FC75" box="[866,949,981,1008]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.8" pageId="2" pageNumber="5" unit="mm" value="28.0">28 mm</quantity>
Body brown and wings pale yellow with dark brown patches.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D22036A6FFD6FFE6B0AFFB9EE25EFB35" blockId="2.[166,1226,981,1424]" pageId="2" pageNumber="5">F e m a l e a b d o m e n. Segment VIII in lateral view with dorsal margin slightly concave, ventral margin with very slight subapical constriction,and with sinuous fingerlike apicoventral lobes; in ventral view triangular and with pair of fingerlike apicoventral lobes blunt apically. Segment IX triangular in lateral view; lateral apodemes extending anteriorly to basal 1/3rd of segment VIII. Vaginal apparatus in ventral view with slight indentation apically.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D22036A6FFD6FFE6B0AFFB3EE4F4FA15" blockId="2.[166,1226,981,1424]" pageId="2" pageNumber="5">
R e m a r k s. The female is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="159F4D25FFD6FFE6B2E3FB3EE59BFB55" authority="(Martynov, 1930)" baseAuthorityName="Martynov" baseAuthorityYear="1930" box="[663,1017,1204,1232]" class="Insecta" family="Rhyacophilidae" genus="Rhyacophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tibetana">
<emphasis id="E0EBEAB4FFD6FFE6B2E3FB3EE57EFB4B" box="[663,796,1204,1230]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="5">H. tibetana</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="B60E4B57FFD6FFE6B35AFB3EE593FB55" author="Martynov, A. V." box="[814,1009,1205,1232]" pageId="2" pageNumber="5" pagination="65 - 112" refId="ref7748" refString="Martynov, A. V. On the trichopterous fauna of China and Eastern Tibet // Proceedings of the Zoological Society of London. - 1930. - 5. - P. 65 - 112." type="book chapter" year="1930">Martynov, 1930</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, from which it is distinguished by the apex of segment VIII which in ventral view is completely divided into lobes, but which in 
<taxonomicName id="159F4D25FFD6FFE6B1E7FB7EE47BFA8B" baseAuthorityName="Martynov" baseAuthorityYear="1930" box="[403,537,1268,1294]" class="Insecta" family="Rhyacophilidae" genus="Rhyacophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tibetana">
<emphasis id="E0EBEAB4FFD6FFE6B1E7FB7EE47BFA8B" box="[403,537,1268,1294]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="5">H. tibetana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is divided only up to the middle of the lobes; the vaginal apparatus has an indentation at its apex whereas the apex is complete and without any indentation in 
<taxonomicName id="159F4D25FFD6FFE6B123FABEE7B9FACB" baseAuthorityName="Martynov" baseAuthorityYear="1930" box="[343,475,1332,1358]" class="Insecta" family="Rhyacophilidae" genus="Rhyacophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tibetana">
<emphasis id="E0EBEAB4FFD6FFE6B123FABEE7B9FACB" box="[343,475,1332,1358]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="5">H. tibetana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Because of lack of sufficient material and the differences given above we hesitate to describe this as a new species on the basis of this female specimen, and prefer to take it as a variant of 
<taxonomicName id="159F4D25FFD6FFE6B27FFAFEE4ECFA0B" baseAuthorityName="Martynov" baseAuthorityYear="1930" box="[523,654,1396,1422]" class="Insecta" family="Rhyacophilidae" genus="Rhyacophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tibetana">
<emphasis id="E0EBEAB4FFD6FFE6B27FFAFEE4ECFA0B" box="[523,654,1396,1422]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="5">H. tibetana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
